José María Alfredo Aznar López (Spanish pronunciation: [xoˈse maˈɾi.a alˈfɾeðo aθˈnar ˈlopeθ] ( listen); born 25 February 1953) served as the Prime Minister of Spain from 1996 to 2004.[1][2] He is a director of News Corporation.



